    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.0-dev-383+g2738f842f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (see \"Expected behavior\")\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.0.9-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n1. Create init file (called here 'init_terminal-no-winscrolled.vim') with the following content:\r\n```vim\r\nau TermOpen * startinsert\r\n\r\nlet g:n = 0\r\nau WinScrolled * let g:n = g:n + 1 | echo g:n\r\n\r\nset noshowmode\r\n```\r\n2. `nvim -u init_terminal-no-winscrolled.vim`\r\n3. `:vsplit term://bash` . It opens terminal buffer in a split while resizing windows. No echo in command line.\r\n4. Press `<C-\\><C-n>`. It leaves Terminal mode and prints 1.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`WinScrolled` should be always emitted when windows scroll/resize occurs. \r\n\r\nThese situations work as expected:\r\n- Remove `au TermOpen * startinsert` from init file and repeat steps. It prints 1 right after vertical split.\r\n- Replace `au TermOpen * startinsert` with `au TerminalOpen * startinsert` and repeat steps with Vim (using `vertical terminal` instead of `vsplit term://bash`). It also prints 1 right after vertical split while also being in Terminal mode.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`WinScrolled` event is emitted right after leaving Terminal mode.",
